WEBVTT

00:00.768 --> 00:02.501
♪♪♪

00:02.570 --> 00:04.903
[clock ticks, alarm rings]

00:04.905 --> 00:06.505
<i> Adult mark: It seemed like</i>
<i> only yesterday</i>

00:06.507 --> 00:09.241
<i> I was dreading the first day</i>
<i> of grade seven.</i>

00:09.310 --> 00:12.578
<i> Now, here I was, dreading</i>
<i> the last day of grade seven.</i>

00:13.647 --> 00:15.714
- Nobody likes change.

00:15.716 --> 00:17.649
<i> Adult mark: Wow.</i>
<i> Pop really got me.</i>

00:17.785 --> 00:19.351
- A one dollar coin?

00:19.353 --> 00:22.120
I mean, what's next?
A twenty-five cent bill?

00:22.156 --> 00:25.490
We'll be the laughingstock
of the united nations!

00:25.559 --> 00:27.359
[bed creaks,
sighs heavily]

00:27.361 --> 00:28.627
[glasses thunk lightly]

00:28.696 --> 00:31.129
[sighs, water pours]
- oh no.

00:31.165 --> 00:33.465
<i> Adult mark: The more things</i>
<i> change.</i>

00:33.600 --> 00:36.167
- [grunts]
- [running footsteps]

00:36.203 --> 00:38.203
[door bangs shut,
music plays on the radio]

00:38.205 --> 00:40.405
- Oh, last day of school, mark.

00:40.441 --> 00:43.542
You won't have to deal with
that crowd all summer.

00:43.544 --> 00:46.044
- Yeah. I guess.
- Good god, mary.

00:46.047 --> 00:47.980
This crowd is eatin' us
out o' house and home.

00:48.115 --> 00:49.415
- Legally you do have
to feed me.

00:49.550 --> 00:51.182
<i>Pop: Well, eat while you can.</i>

00:51.218 --> 00:53.651
Because when word gets out
about this funny money,

00:53.687 --> 00:56.154
We're headed for another
great depression.

00:56.223 --> 00:58.022
Mark my words.

00:58.059 --> 00:59.458
Mike jr.: Hey.

01:01.295 --> 01:02.894
[cereal jingles]
- take it easy, will ya?

01:02.963 --> 01:05.664
It's not bottomless!

01:05.799 --> 01:08.300
- I found some interesting
reading material in your room.

01:08.369 --> 01:10.902
- [clears throat] did you?!
Well, uh, it's, it's not mine,

01:10.971 --> 01:12.770
I can assure you o' that.
I just uh...

01:12.807 --> 01:14.939
Oh. Uh... Yeah, yeah.

01:14.975 --> 01:16.608
<i> - The university</i>
<i> of new brunswick?</i>

01:16.743 --> 01:18.776
But... It's so far away!

01:18.913 --> 01:20.578
- Maybe in September?

01:20.614 --> 01:22.948
- Who needs university?
- Or not.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.516
I dunno, just give it back.

01:24.552 --> 01:27.285
- I dropped out of school
to fish when I was mark's age.

01:27.287 --> 01:29.254
- Yes. Because your father
drowned.

01:29.323 --> 01:31.590
- At least it put hairs
on my chest.

01:31.659 --> 01:33.392
You could do with
a little toughening up,

01:33.527 --> 01:36.094
Let me tell ya.
- Yeah, you're probably right.

01:36.097 --> 01:37.329
I probably would've been
better off

01:37.464 --> 01:39.531
If my father had drowned, too.

01:39.533 --> 01:41.833
Mark: [chuckles] you'd be
the first person in the family

01:41.836 --> 01:43.434
To get off the island.

01:43.471 --> 01:45.737
- Yeah, but you'll get murdered
out there.

01:45.739 --> 01:47.772
- Yeah, and you'll never get
the body back.

01:47.774 --> 01:50.909
Tanya bursey died in florida
visiting her sister.

01:51.044 --> 01:52.977
<i> They had to bury her</i>
<i> in buffalo.</i>

01:53.013 --> 01:54.879
Mickey mouse ears and all.

01:54.881 --> 01:56.415
- I don't know.

01:56.417 --> 01:58.283
Room and board on top
of tuition?

01:58.285 --> 02:00.418
I mean, where the hell's
the money coming from?

02:00.420 --> 02:02.621
- This is exactly why
I wanna get outta here!

02:02.623 --> 02:04.756
And stop snooping through
my room!

02:07.027 --> 02:08.961
[footsteps recede,
music plays quietly]

02:08.963 --> 02:10.696
- Can you, uh,
drive me to the bank?

02:10.698 --> 02:13.498
I wanna get some bills
before the rioting starts.

02:13.534 --> 02:15.099
<i> [bedroom door bangs shut]</i>

02:16.270 --> 02:18.770
- Overall, you did very well
on your math tests.

02:18.772 --> 02:20.305
Especially you, ritchie.

02:20.307 --> 02:22.441
Hmm.

02:24.512 --> 02:26.811
Mark, could be worse.
Barely.

02:26.881 --> 02:28.613
Report cards come out Friday,

02:28.682 --> 02:30.848
Followed by the school dance.

02:30.885 --> 02:34.118
Remember to leave room for
the holy ghost while dancing.

02:34.155 --> 02:36.421
[student chuckles, bell rings]
adult mark: The school dance!

02:36.423 --> 02:38.657
<i> I had finally gotten up</i>
<i> the nerve to ask fox,</i>

02:38.726 --> 02:40.758
<i> And the thought of it</i>
<i> made my heart beat faster</i>

02:40.794 --> 02:42.260
<i> Than any gym class.</i>

02:42.329 --> 02:44.028
- Hey! Are you going
to the dance?

02:44.064 --> 02:45.864
- I can't dance with girls.

02:45.999 --> 02:48.066
Or even be in the same room
as girls dancin'.

02:48.068 --> 02:50.135
- [chuckles]
well, it might be fun.

02:50.137 --> 02:52.303
Besides, you can go with me.

02:53.908 --> 02:55.740
Uh, fox?

02:55.809 --> 02:59.277
Uh, are you thinking of maybe
pondering the idea of--

02:59.346 --> 03:01.346
<i> Sister margaret: Fox!</i>

03:01.348 --> 03:03.881
May I speak with you
for a moment?

03:03.918 --> 03:05.684
[indistinct chatter]

03:05.686 --> 03:07.151
- [sighs heavily]

03:09.857 --> 03:11.990
- And today's vocm question
of the day:

03:12.026 --> 03:13.559
"do you believe predictions

03:13.694 --> 03:15.493
Of a possible collapse
of the cod fishery?"

03:15.629 --> 03:17.328
Our lines are open.
Your thoughts.

03:17.364 --> 03:18.964
Line one, you're on the air.

03:19.033 --> 03:20.499
<i> Elderly lady: Mike? Hello?</i>

03:20.634 --> 03:22.901
Is that you? [feedback squeals]
- turn down your radio, caller.

03:22.903 --> 03:24.336
<i> Elderly lady: Oh, I can't hear</i>
<i> you, mike.</i>

03:24.471 --> 03:26.171
<i> I'm getting feedback</i>
<i> from me radio.</i>

03:26.240 --> 03:27.773
- Our question of the day:

03:27.908 --> 03:29.641
Do you believe predictions
of an imminent collapse

03:29.677 --> 03:31.777
Of the cod fishery?
Your thoughts.

03:31.779 --> 03:33.845
<i> Elderly lady: I wanted</i>
<i> to report me lost cat.</i>

03:33.847 --> 03:35.313
- [whispers] turn it down.
- [whispers] go!

03:35.382 --> 03:38.049
<i> - She's a white tabby,</i>
<i> with a big puffy--</i>

03:38.085 --> 03:39.918
[button clicks]
will you get outta here?

03:40.053 --> 03:41.253
- Go to commercial.
This is important.

03:41.388 --> 03:43.121
- More important than
the vocm

03:43.190 --> 03:44.723
Question of the day, is it?

03:44.792 --> 03:46.858
<i> Elderly lady: She answers to</i>
<i> puss, but her name is jacinta.</i>

03:46.994 --> 03:48.727
<i> I put food out,</i>
<i> but only got the hard</i>

03:48.729 --> 03:50.829
<i> And she likes the wet--</i>
<i> [button clicks]</i>

03:50.964 --> 03:52.798
- We seem to have lost you,
caller.

03:52.800 --> 03:55.801
We'll be right back with
your thoughts... After this.

03:55.803 --> 03:57.469
<i>Commercial: At caul's funeral</i>
<i> home,</i>

03:57.538 --> 03:59.271
<i> Your loved one is more</i>
<i> than just a dead body--</i>

03:59.406 --> 04:01.306
[lowers volume]
- this better be good!

04:01.308 --> 04:03.541
- Your career's gonna end
in that funeral home, buddy.

04:03.543 --> 04:05.477
I just overheard the bosses
in the bathroom.

04:05.479 --> 04:07.412
They never knew I was there.
I was in the stall.

04:07.481 --> 04:09.147
Been having some trouble.

04:09.149 --> 04:10.715
Doctor says I need
to lay off the dairy,

04:10.751 --> 04:12.684
But you know how it is--
- will you get to the point?!

04:12.720 --> 04:14.753
- They said, and I quote,
"it's gonna be

04:14.755 --> 04:16.421
A whole new station.
All music. No talk."

04:16.423 --> 04:18.557
- No talk?!
But I'm the "talk."

04:18.692 --> 04:20.225
Uh, somebody would've said
something!

04:20.360 --> 04:21.760
- No, they're not gonna
tell you!

04:21.762 --> 04:23.361
You're the first one
they're gonna get rid of.

04:23.430 --> 04:25.430
Not me.
I know how to spin records.

04:25.432 --> 04:27.098
- Just because I don't spin
records

04:27.167 --> 04:29.367
Doesn't mean my work here
isn't valuable, dick.

04:29.436 --> 04:31.169
[button clicks]
- and we're back!

04:31.171 --> 04:33.237
Line two, you're on the air!
Our vocm question of the day:

04:33.274 --> 04:34.772
"will the cod fishery
collapse?"

04:34.808 --> 04:36.508
Your thoughts?
Caller: Mike!

04:36.577 --> 04:38.443
<i> I think I found</i>
<i> that lady's cat.</i>

04:38.445 --> 04:40.312
I just said, "here, puss, puss"
- [sighs]

04:40.314 --> 04:41.913
<i>- And it came right up to me.</i>

04:42.983 --> 04:44.683
♪♪♪

04:44.818 --> 04:46.051
- [gasps]

04:46.186 --> 04:47.652
- I need you to be
my math tutor.

04:47.688 --> 04:49.253
- You want my help?

04:49.290 --> 04:50.756
- If I don't do the nun's
stupid make-up test,

04:50.891 --> 04:52.791
Then I can't go to the dance.

04:52.860 --> 04:55.394
And if you tell anyone,
I'm gonna kick your ass so hard

04:55.529 --> 04:57.995
You'll be tasting my sneakers
all summer.

04:58.032 --> 05:00.865
- M'lady.
- What'd you call me?

05:00.901 --> 05:03.068
- Nothing!
Can we chat later?

05:03.137 --> 05:04.469
I could save you a seat
on the bus.

05:04.538 --> 05:06.471
We could have a drink
and a chin wag

05:06.473 --> 05:08.840
About the upcoming soiree?

05:08.842 --> 05:11.176
[juice sloshes]

05:11.311 --> 05:12.944
- Leave me alone!

05:14.148 --> 05:16.081
[footsteps recede]

05:16.150 --> 05:19.051
- [sighs] hey, did she say
if she was going to the dance?

05:20.520 --> 05:22.286
- [nervous gasps]

05:22.323 --> 05:23.521
[sucking up juice]

05:26.326 --> 05:28.025
I need to go to the toilet.

05:28.062 --> 05:29.528
<i> Adult mark: I wasn't great</i>
<i> at math,</i>

05:29.663 --> 05:31.763
<i> But I knew when something</i>
<i> wasn't adding up.</i>

05:31.832 --> 05:33.598
[rock music plays loudly]

05:33.600 --> 05:35.500
[door clicks open]

05:35.502 --> 05:37.235
- What're you listening to?

05:37.304 --> 05:39.170
- Okay, fine,
I'll put headphones on.

05:39.206 --> 05:41.172
- What? No, no, no, no!
I wanna hear that.

05:41.241 --> 05:44.910
Is this this, uh, duran fellow
with the hungry wolf?

05:45.045 --> 05:46.745
- Here you go, mike.
Nice and clean.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.413
- Thanks.

05:48.548 --> 05:50.448
- Well, you know where you're
not gonna get clean laundry

05:50.517 --> 05:52.250
Done for you, hmm?
New brunswick.

05:52.319 --> 05:53.451
- Do you mind?
We're talking music.

05:53.520 --> 05:55.453
- Hey, can you guys get outta
my room?

05:55.489 --> 05:57.255
I just wanna be alone.

05:57.257 --> 05:59.190
- Come and have a gander
at your inheritance.

06:01.895 --> 06:04.262
- Ten dollars?
- Ah, yes, now.

06:04.331 --> 06:06.998
But when they take these bills
out of circulation,

06:07.067 --> 06:08.800
This could double in value!

06:09.936 --> 06:12.170
- So twenty dollars.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.340
- Uh, can you lend me
some change?

06:16.377 --> 06:17.809
I need to go down
to the duke of duckworths.

06:17.878 --> 06:20.144
- You got $10 dollars!
- I can't touch that!

06:20.180 --> 06:21.546
That's an investment!
- Oh, sweet jesus,

06:21.548 --> 06:23.281
Will you stop fightin'!

06:23.417 --> 06:25.150
Any wonder he wants to move
away, right, mike?

06:25.219 --> 06:26.918
Little bugger.

06:27.054 --> 06:29.020
Kids: [indistinct chatter
and laughter]

06:29.056 --> 06:32.691
- So if 3x + 1 = 16,

06:32.826 --> 06:34.525
How do we solve for x?

06:38.298 --> 06:40.965
[loud snap]
- [frustrated sigh]

06:40.967 --> 06:42.700
That pencil was strawberry
sniff!

06:42.836 --> 06:45.336
- Screw it. My brothers
all repeated grades.

06:45.372 --> 06:47.706
Makes sense.
I'm stupid too.

06:47.841 --> 06:50.041
- You're not failing
because you're stupid.

06:50.077 --> 06:52.243
You're failing because
you're not trying!

06:52.279 --> 06:54.312
Trust me, you'll get it.

06:54.448 --> 06:56.481
Just don't give up, okay?

06:58.719 --> 07:00.418
- [sighs]

07:00.454 --> 07:02.320
[chair scrapes]

07:03.990 --> 07:05.924
♪♪♪

07:05.993 --> 07:08.125
<i> Adult mark: Betrayed</i>
<i> by the only person I knew</i>

07:08.127 --> 07:10.128
<i> Who was more of a geek</i>
<i> than I was.</i>

07:10.263 --> 07:11.663
<i> She certainly had a type.</i>

07:13.267 --> 07:14.666
- Well, isn't this romantic?
[paper rustles]

07:14.735 --> 07:16.534
- Ew! Gross!

07:16.570 --> 07:18.402
- It's not what you think.
The truth--

07:18.439 --> 07:21.138
- Is none of his business.
Leave us alone!

07:22.342 --> 07:23.741
- Fine.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.610
But you can forget about going
to the dance together,

07:25.612 --> 07:27.612
'cause I'm not going anymore.

07:27.614 --> 07:29.247
[huffs]

07:29.316 --> 07:31.016
- You never asked me
to the dance.

07:31.151 --> 07:33.284
- He was talking to me.

07:37.290 --> 07:38.823
[record jacket squeaks]

07:38.892 --> 07:41.226
- Hey, dick, have you got
a minute?

07:41.361 --> 07:44.296
Good god!
You were right!

07:44.298 --> 07:46.598
- Told ya. You're toast.
- I can't lose this job.

07:46.600 --> 07:48.833
Young mike's talking
about university.

07:48.836 --> 07:50.735
- Don't forget you live
in a company house.

07:50.737 --> 07:52.970
You get fired,
you're homeless, too.

07:53.006 --> 07:55.707
You wanna work? You're gonna
have to learn to spin records.

07:55.842 --> 07:59.010
I was gonna dj the school
dance. Why don't you do it?

07:59.145 --> 08:01.313
Better to make your mistake
in front of nobody who matters.

08:01.448 --> 08:03.114
- That's my son's dance.
- Yes,

08:03.150 --> 08:05.283
But your son already knows
you're a...

08:06.320 --> 08:08.152
Great guy.

08:10.957 --> 08:13.859
<i> Remember, no elevator music!</i>
<i> Just hits!</i>

08:13.994 --> 08:16.294
[drawer scrapes shut]
pop: Where did it go?

08:16.296 --> 08:19.397
I left my money on
the dresser last night.

08:19.466 --> 08:20.932
Good god.

08:22.736 --> 08:24.703
I've lost one
of my dollar bills.

08:24.705 --> 08:26.604
Have you seen it?
- No.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.874
- Well, it didn't just
fly away.

08:29.009 --> 08:31.609
If I was to look in there,
would I find it?

08:31.645 --> 08:33.945
- Of course not! Wait, what?
What're you doing?

08:34.080 --> 08:35.947
- [grunts] hmm...
- Pop!

08:35.983 --> 08:37.615
- Well, it must be somewhere?
- I-I...

08:37.684 --> 08:40.285
- Oh, well, I don't see it.
What about your pocket?

08:40.287 --> 08:41.953
- No! No!
- Let me look in your pocket!

08:41.989 --> 08:43.989
- Get off me! Get--
- ow! Come here!

08:43.991 --> 08:45.690
- I got it! [sprays]
- what the hell is that?!

08:45.726 --> 08:47.559
- What is all this racket?

08:47.694 --> 08:49.627
- [coughs] oh, it's just--
- oh!

08:49.663 --> 08:52.630
- This house is too small!
I need some privacy.

08:52.666 --> 08:54.366
- When mike goes,
I want his room!

08:54.368 --> 08:55.767
- Do you two know how lucky
you are

08:55.902 --> 08:57.435
To have a roof over your head
at all?

08:57.504 --> 08:58.970
- Mike! They're just skylarkin'
is all.

08:58.972 --> 09:00.438
- Enough!
- What's gotten into you?

09:00.507 --> 09:02.073
- Nothing is good enough
for you crowd.

09:02.142 --> 09:04.242
You wanna go live with mike?
Fine! [trunk clunks]

09:04.377 --> 09:06.545
You got it! Come on!
- What're you doing?

09:06.680 --> 09:08.213
[bed drags]

09:08.348 --> 09:10.916
- If pop isn't mature enough
to have a roommate,

09:11.051 --> 09:12.784
Then you can go stay with
your brother. Come on!

09:12.919 --> 09:14.819
- Uh... Wait! What?
[bed drags]

09:16.690 --> 09:19.290
[crickets chirp,
dog barks in the distance]

09:22.195 --> 09:24.129
Mike? You up?

09:27.334 --> 09:29.267
[light clicks on]

09:31.038 --> 09:33.204
Mike? You up?

09:33.206 --> 09:35.340
- [sighs]

09:35.475 --> 09:37.141
What do you want?

09:38.779 --> 09:40.978
- I think I like this girl...

09:42.282 --> 09:44.482
Who ritchie likes,

09:45.586 --> 09:47.151
And she likes ritchie.

09:47.187 --> 09:48.953
And it was just--
[pillow thuds]

09:48.956 --> 09:50.622
- Go to sleep!

09:51.858 --> 09:53.625
<i> Adult mark: The thing about</i>
<i> change is,</i>

09:53.627 --> 09:56.093
<i> You don't know what you got</i>
<i> till it's gone.</i>

09:58.732 --> 10:00.765
[bed creaks]

10:03.904 --> 10:05.637
- [sighs heavily]

10:05.706 --> 10:07.505
[crow caws]

10:07.574 --> 10:13.444
♪♪♪

10:13.480 --> 10:19.050
♪♪♪

10:19.086 --> 10:20.719
- Marcus.

10:20.854 --> 10:22.454
- Grandfather.

10:22.589 --> 10:23.688
[lid clicks]

10:23.823 --> 10:25.523
[juice pours]
- [spits]

10:26.760 --> 10:28.726
[juice pours]
- whoa!

10:29.763 --> 10:32.397
Going a bit heavy
on that juice there, son.

10:32.399 --> 10:34.332
<i> Rough day ahead?</i>

10:34.467 --> 10:36.600
- Bit of nerves about
the dance.

10:36.637 --> 10:38.402
Not that you care,
I'm sure.

10:38.438 --> 10:40.038
- Mm.

10:40.107 --> 10:43.074
- [gulps] mmm...
- [sighs heavily]

10:43.209 --> 10:45.209
[glass clunks]
- ah...

10:45.245 --> 10:47.345
[bill rustles and snaps]

10:50.784 --> 10:52.483
- There.
- Well,

10:52.519 --> 10:54.219
I can't take one
of your special dollars.

10:54.354 --> 10:56.454
- I want you to have it.

10:56.523 --> 10:58.490
- So I can save it?
- No!

10:58.625 --> 11:00.491
I want you to live
in the moment!

11:00.527 --> 11:04.362
Buy your girl a soft drink
at the dance.

11:06.299 --> 11:08.232
- I can't dance.
- What?!

11:08.301 --> 11:10.768
The critch men were always
the best dancers.

11:12.839 --> 11:15.907
Listen, you get onto
the dance floor, right?

11:15.909 --> 11:19.110
Your shoulders back,
your spine over your ass,

11:19.245 --> 11:21.346
And put your hands
down by your sides,

11:21.481 --> 11:23.114
And then you kick your feet out

11:23.116 --> 11:24.849
Like you're busting for a whiz.

11:24.851 --> 11:27.618
[hums "I'se the b'y"]

11:29.222 --> 11:31.189
- ♪ I'se the b'y
who builds the boat ♪

11:31.191 --> 11:33.058
♪ and I'se the b'y
who sails her ♪

11:33.193 --> 11:34.793
♪ I'se the b'y
who catches the fish ♪

11:34.928 --> 11:37.161
- Head up! Head up!
- ♪ ...Home to liza

11:37.197 --> 11:39.431
<i> Adult mark: Pop was right.</i>
<i> I had to live in the moment.</i>

